commit_list.message: small bit of cleanup and polish
added some meta to the head
1.5.12 - added mixin for css3 box-sizing and added said mixin to reset lib file for textareas. WOAH
1.5.11 - an oversite with variable scoping remedied
1.5.10 - did you know rails 3 uses haml :format html5 by default? that means i don't need the line in my initializer file. now i know, and knowing is half the battle.
1.5.9 - added css3 column mixins, added opera vendor syntax to transition and transform mixin, added some commenting
1.5.8 - this is really just some very misc cleanup here and there. removed some of the versions in the gemfile.
1.5.7 - moved vendor specific css3 attributes BEFORE spec attribute in mixins library
1.5.6 -- check the github page, too many little things for a comment message
reorganized sass dir, updated extend to include reset sass and updated README file
1.5.4 - everyone is saying webkit font smoothing set to antialiased is the worst thing to do ever. i better listen to cool kids.
1.5.3 - added sass to the lib to stop button active states from getting outlined in FF. also added some new @extend classes, and moved them all into their own extend sass file
1.5.2 - converted a few mixins into @extend classes. updated documentation
1.5.1 - added some additional classes to be used with @extend, for better organization
few changes to layout file, and added desciption meta tag
cleanup and some reorganization of mobile styles, layout haml etc
updated gemfile, some additions to the reset, and added in a commented out thing for ie9.js if you want it.
sass wonderful clean up of joy and such
wow, a typo in the readme i never noticed. how long has it been there i wonder?
oh, update version # would be good, too
added hampton's fork, use some @extend fun in _common and a little bit of tidy up
lots of misc cleanup and fixes
added some more mobile media stuff and other misc cleanup
1.3.2 -- updated mobile sass file, and some additional info in the snippets file
v1.2.2 - some sass cleaned and added some new sass to reset for default textarea behaviour
added a proper native jquery browser detector plugin to application.js
added the fancy optimizeLegibility for text-rendering
added a new font size, woaaaaaah
